olive oil
1 packet penne
3 clove garlic
½ bunch baby broccoli
1 packet diced bacon
1 sachet Classic Roast Seasoning
1 packet Diced Tomatoes with Garlic & Onion
½ tsp salt
½ packet cream
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Half-fill a large saucepan with water, add a generous pinch of salt, then bring to the boil over high heat.
• Cook penne in the boiling water until ‘al dente’, 12 minutes.
• Reserve some pasta water (1/2 cup for 2 people / 1 cup for 4 people), then drain and return to the pan with a drizzle of olive oil to prevent sticking.

Little cooks: Older kids can help add the pasta to the saucepan under adult supervision. Be careful, the water is boiling!

• Meanwhile, finely chop garlic.
• Trim and cut baby broccoli into thirds.

• Preheat the grill to high. Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook diced bacon, breaking up with a spoon, until golden, 6-7 minutes.
• Add baby broccoli and cook until lightly browned, 2-3 minutes.

• Add garlic and Classic Roast seasoning and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add crushed & sieved tomatoes, chicken-style stock powder, cream (see ingredients) and reserved pasta water. Simmer until slightly thickened, 2-3 minutes.

• Stir baby spinach leaves and cooked penne through the sauce, then transfer to a baking dish.
• Evenly sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.
• Bake until golden, 5-7 minutes.

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling the cheese on top. Careful the pasta sauce is hot!

• Divide creamy bacon and veggie pasta bake between bowls. Enjoy!